$$

Given that the state equation of a certain linear time-invariant system is 
$$\dot{x} =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 1 \\
-2 & -3
\end{bmatrix}x +
\begin{bmatrix}
0 \\
1
\end{bmatrix}u$$
with the initial condition $x(0)=\left[\begin{array}{ll}-1 & 0\end{array}\right]^T$, find the expression for the state response $x(t)$ of the system to a unit step input signal.
Options:
A. All other answers are incorrect
B. \mathbf{x}(t) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{1}{5} - \frac{3}{2} e^{-2t} + \frac{1}{3} e^{-3t} \\ 3 e^{-2t} - 3 e^{-3t} \end{bmatrix}
C. \mathbf{x}(t) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{1}{5} - \frac{3}{2} e^{-2t} - \frac{1}{3} e^{-3t} \\ 3 e^{-2t} + 3 e^{-3t} \end{bmatrix}
D. \mathbf{x}(t) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{1}{5} - \frac{3}{2} e^{-2t} \\ 3 e^{-2t} - 3 e^{-3t} \end{bmatrix}
E. \mathbf{x}(t) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{1}{5} + \frac{3}{2} e^{-2t} + \frac{1}{3} e^{-3t} \\ 3 e^{-2t} - 3 e^{-3t} \end{bmatrix}
F. \mathbf{x}(t) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{1}{5} - \frac{3}{2} e^{-2t} + \frac{1}{3} e^{-3t} \\ 3 e^{-2t} + 3 e^{-3t} \end{bmatrix}

