Given the state-space expression of the system 
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\dot{\boldsymbol{x}}=A x+b u \\
y=\boldsymbol{c}^{\mathrm{T}} \boldsymbol{x}+d u
\end{array}
$$
,where $\boldsymbol{A}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}3 & 2 \\ -2 & -1\end{array}\right], \boldsymbol{b}=\left[\begin{array}{l}4 \\ 3\end{array}\right], \boldsymbol{c}^{\mathrm{T}}=\left[\begin{array}{ll}2 & 1\end{array}\right], \boldsymbol{d}=1$, find the transfer function $G(s)$ of the system.
